text:
SimCorp Ukraine - Entry level Software engineer
— At least Bachelor’s degree in computer sciences, engineering, physics, mathematics;
— Ability to work with complex architecture, front and back-end;
— Practical programming experience is an advantage;

You see yourself as a person with:
— A good sense of quality, ability to work to deadlines, taking ownership of produced solution;
— Good team player, valuing team goals over personal achievements; 
— Intermediate level of English (spoken and written).

Пропонуємо

You will be a member of a self-organized team consisting of developers, testers and business experts in Kiev, Ukraine. The team is responsible for delivering functionality within the ABOR area. The respective code is based mainly on APL. You also expect to interact with colleagues from Copenhagen (Denmark) and Bad Homburg (Germany) through communities of practice.

After working successfully as a trainee, you receive a good chance to be offered a full-time job.

Обов’язки

After comprehensive onboarding program you will be involved in the development process, including: 
— Assisting team in delivering enhanced ABOR modules and reaching team objectives;
— Constantly learn and improve yourself, the team and our product.
Apply here:

